    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>Current military tracking data reveals heightened US and Israeli military activity across multiple theaters. The USS Gerald R. Ford returned to Norfolk on May 17, 2026, after a 326-day deployment, emphasizing the strain on naval resources with simultaneous CSG operations. Israel&#39;s F-35s are receiving external fuel tanks, indicating improvements in their capabilities and readiness for future operations. The UAE is constructing massive &#39;Cope Cages&#39; to protect its energy facilities from Iranian drone attacks, highlighting strategic security measures.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
